## Create the data source that will link Red Dog and the database

One way to do this in Tomcat is to define the datasource in `context.xml`.

Create `$CATALINA_HOME/webapps/rdap/META-INF/context.xml`, insert the following content and replace the dummy values (in square brackets):

	<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
	<Context path="/rdap">
		<Resource name="jdbc/rdap"
			type="javax.sql.DataSource"
			auth="Container"
			driverClassName="com.mysql.jdbc.Driver"
			url="[URL]"
			username="[username]"
			password="[password]"
			validationQuery="select 1 from dual" />
	</Context>

